article.headline: Coppin St 68, South Carolina St 67 (OT)
article.story: ORANGEBURG, S.C. (AP) -- Talmadge Bell scored 18 points, including a critical 3-pointer in overtime, as Coppin State beat South Carolina State 68-67 Monday night. Bell's jumper put the Eagles (5-13, 5-2 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) ahead 67-62 with 3:25 to go. Coppin State scored only one more point the rest of the way, but hung on for the victory. The Bulldogs (5-12, 3-4) trailed for much of the game, but held Coppin State scoreless for the final 2:28 and forced overtime on Brian Mason's putback with six seconds to go in the second half. Turnovers killed the Bulldogs, who gave the ball away 25 times compared to 12 turnovers for the Eagles. Tywain McKee led Coppin State with 19 points, while Darryl Proctor added nine points and 11 rebounds. Mason had 20 points and nine rebounds and Thurman Zimmerman pulled down 15 rebounds for South Carolina State.
